object.script:
-- Track the rate of battery and fuel consumption -- Display the rate and duration remaining for each in minutes
function gn(n) return input.getNumber(n) end
function sn(n,v) output.setNumber(n,v) end
function state_obj() return {prev=0,cur=0,rate=0} end
updateticks=120 -- Ticks between updates, 60/sec batstate=state_obj() fuelstate=state_obj()
function update(state,v) state.prev=state.cur state.cur=v state.rate=(state.cur-state.prev) * updateticks / 60 -- Track rate in d/sec end
clock=0 function onTick() clock=clock+1 fuel=gn(1) bat=gn(2)*100
if clock>=updateticks then update(fuelstate,fuel) update(batstate,bat) clock=0 end sn(1,fuelstate.rate) sn(2,fuel/fuelstate.rate) sn(3,batstate.rate) sn(4,bat/batstate.rate) end
posx=property.getNumber("Pos X") posy=property.getNumber("Pos Y") function timestr(sec) if sec>=math.huge or sec<=-math.huge then return "--:--:--" else return string.format("%02.0f:%02.0f:%02.0f",sec/3600,(sec/60)%60,sec%60) end end
function onDraw() local str=string.format("BAT : %3.0f%% %+5.2f\n" .. "T : %s\n" .. "FUEL: %4.0fL %+2.2f\n" .. "T : %s\n" .. "RATES/MIN", bat,batstate.rate*60,timestr(-bat/batstate.rate), fuel,fuelstate.rate*60,timestr(-fuel/fuelstate.rate)) screen.setColor(0,0,153) screen.drawText(posx,posy,str) end

object.script:
function gn(x) return input.getNumber(x) end
function gb(x) return input.getBool(x) end
function onTick() clutch=gb(1) bat=gn(2) temp=gn(3) speed=gn(5) rpm=gn(6) gear=gn(7) end
colw=5 rowh=6
function gear_name(x) if x==0 then return "N" elseif x==-1 then return "R" else return string.format("D%.0f",x) end end
function rg(bool) local c={0,255}
if bool then c[1]=255 c[2]=0 end screen.setColor(c[1],c[2],0) end
function onDraw()
local str
w=screen.getWidth() h=screen.getHeight() y=2
str=string.format("%5.0f KPH\n%5.0f RPM", speed, rpm) screen.setColor(0,255,0) screen.drawTextBox(0,y,w,rowh,str)
rg(temp>95) screen.drawTextBox(0,y+rowh*2,w,rowh,string.format("%3.2fC",temp))
rg(bat<25) screen.drawTextBox(0,y+rowh*3,w,rowh,string.format("%3.2f BAT",bat))
screen.setColor(0,255,0) screen.drawTextBox(0,y+rowh*4,w,rowh,string.format("GEAR %s",gear_name(gear)))
--[[ if clutch then screen.setColor(255,0,0) end screen.drawTextBox(colw*7,y+rowh*4,w,rowh,"CLUTCH") --]] end

object.script:
-- 23-gear near-CV manual transmission representing all meaningful -- gear combinations from two 7-speed gearbox units connected in series.
-- 1,6,16,22 all_gears={ {1,1,r=1}, {1,2,r=1.2}, {2,2,r=1.44}, {1,3,r=1.5}, {1,4,r=1.8}, {1,5,r=2}, {2,4,r=2.16}, {3,3,r=2.25}, {2,5,r=2.4}, {1,6,r=2.5}, {3,4,r=2.7}, {1,7,r=3}, {4,4,r=3.24}, {4,5,r=3.6}, {3,6,r=3.75}, {5,5,r=4}, {4,6,r=4.5}, {5,6,r=5}, {4,7,r=5.4}, {5,7,r=6}, {6,6,r=6.25}, {6,7,r=7.5}, {7,7,r=9} }
all_gears[-1]={7,7,r=-1} all_gears[0]={0,0,r=0}
function parse_gear(prog,i,j) local x if not i.v then return nil end j.v=string.find(prog,",",i.v) x=tonumber( string.sub(prog,i.v,j.v and j.v-1) ) i.v=j.v and j.v+1 return x end
function check_for_neutral(prog,i,j,result) local g=parse_gear(prog,i,j) if not g then return nil end if g==0 then result[0]=0 end end
mingear=0 maxgear=0
function countgears() maxgear=#shift_pattern
if shift_pattern[-1] then mingear=-1 elseif shift_pattern[0] then mingear=0 else mingear=1 end end
shift_pattern={} function parse_program(prog) local i={v=1} local j={v=nil} local g
-- R and N g=parse_gear(prog,i,j) if not g then shift_pattern=all_gears return end
if g==-1 then shift_pattern[-1]=all_gears[-1] g=parse_gear(prog,i,j) end
if not g then return end if g==0 then shift_pattern[0]=all_gears[0] end ----
repeat g=parse_gear(prog,i,j) if g then shift_pattern[#shift_pattern+1]=all_gears[g] end until not g end
parse_program(property.getText("gear program")) countgears()
function sn(n,v) output.setNumber(n,v) end
function sb(n,v) output.setBool(n,v) end
function gn(n) return input.getNumber(n) end
function gb(n) return input.getBool(n) end
function pgn(k) return property.getNumber(k) end
clutchbegin=pgn("clutch begin") clutchengage=pgn("clutch engage") clutchscale=clutchengage-clutchbegin hithrottle=pgn("at high throttle") cruiselo=pgn("cruise low") cruisehi=pgn("cruise high") maxrpm=pgn("max rpm") gearbias=pgn("gear bias") wait=pgn("shift delay")*60
-- Calculate a score for how favorable the specified gear is function check_gear(n) if n<1 or n>#shift_pattern then return -math.huge end local thisgear=shift_pattern[gear] local thatgear=shift_pattern[n] local newrpm=rpm*thisgear.r/thatgear.r local x if newrpm>hirpm then x=hirpm-newrpm elseif newrpm<lorpm then x=newrpm-lorpm elseif downshift then x=newrpm else x=hirpm-newrpm end return x end
downshift=false hirpm=0 lorpm=0 rpm=0 uclock=0 dclock=0 function onTick() local up,down,clutch,selup,seldown local a,b,s,s2,s3 gear=math.floor(gn(1)) rpm=gn(2)*60 throttle=gn(3)
-- Clutch clutch=(rpm-clutchbegin)/clutchscale sn(4,clutch)
-- Downshift? downshift=throttle>hithrottle if downshift then lorpm=cruisehi hirpm=maxrpm else lorpm=cruiselo hirpm=cruisehi end
s=check_gear(gear)+gearbias b=gear s2=0 s3=s
if gear>=1 then for i=1,#shift_pattern do s2=check_gear(i) if s2>s3 then sd=s2-s s3=s2 b=i end end end
if b<gear then dclock=(dclock+1)%wait down=dclock<1 -- clock=0 --down=true else dclock=0 end
if b>gear then uclock=(uclock+1)%wait up=uclock<1 -- up=true else uclock=0 end
-- Reverse sb(2,gear==-1)
-- Kept in register selup=gb(1) seldown=gb(2)
if selup and gear<1 then up=true down=false end if seldown then if gear>0 then gear=1 end down=true up=false end
if up then gear=math.min(gear+1,maxgear) end if down then gear=math.max(gear-1,mingear) end sn(1,gear) sb(1,up or down)
obj=shift_pattern[gear] if obj==nil then obj=shift_pattern[1] end sn(2, obj[2] ) -- Drive gear sn(3, obj[1] ) -- Pinion cluster end
function onDraw()
local s=string.format("GEAR: %.0f ",gear) for i=1,#shift_pattern do s=s .. string.format("%.0f:%.0f ",i,check_gear(i)) end screen.setColor(0,255,0) screen.drawTextBox(0,0,screen.getWidth(),screen.getHeight(),s) end

object.script:
-- Watch the direction of torque transfer, and if the load is driving the engine -- rpm downward, then reduce the clutch pressure so that the differential can equalize at a target -- rate and avoid a jolt from excessive engine braking. Prevents the upshift jolt from jerking -- the transmission back into low gear, or oscillating back and forth between two gears.
function gn(n) return input.getNumber(n) end
function pgn(k) return property.getNumber(k) end
function sn(n,v) output.setNumber(n,v) end
-- Clutch must be left slightly open so that we can sense which way the torque is transferring -- Would be nice if torque sensors had a notion of negative torque, but they don't. maxclutch=pgn("max clutch") minclutch=pgn("min clutch")
-- The drive-side (negative) acceleration rate which triggers decoupling trigger=pgn("trigger rpm/s")
-- How to scale the amount of decoupling. 1 is proportional to the rate of -- drive-side deceleration with respect to the trigger rate, so that double the -- trigger deceleration results in half-decoupling. So, this is scales that rate. factor=pgn("release factor")
-- Maximum decoupling at this rpm delta maxrpmd=pgn("max rpm/sd") clutch=maxclutch
function clamp(x,l,h) return math.max(math.min(x,h),l) end
function onTick() driverpm=gn(1)*60 driverpmd=gn(2)*60*60 loadrpm=gn(3)*60 loadrpmd=gn(4)*60*60 local dd,trate
if (loadrpm<driverpm and loadrpmd<0) then clutch=clamp(1-(loadrpm-driverpm)/maxrpmd,0,1)*(maxclutch-minclutch)+minclutch --clutch=clamp(1+(driverpmd*factor/maxrpmd),0,1)*(maxclutch-minclutch)+minclutch elseif driverpm<loadrpm and loadrpmd<trigger then -- Decouple to avoid engine braking clutch=minclutch -- if loadrpmd<trigger then clutch=minclutch end --clutch=clamp(1+(loadrpmd*factor/maxrpmd),minclutch,maxclutch) else clutch=maxclutch end sn(1,clutch) end
function onDraw() end

object.script:
function gn(n) return input.getNumber(n) end
function sb(n,v) output.setBool(n,v) end
function gb(n) return input.getBool(n) end
function sn(n,v) output.setNumber(n,v) end
function clamp(n, low, high) return math.min(math.max(n, low), high) end
zoomq=5 screenid=property.getNumber("Screen ID") function onTick()
sb(32,gb(32))
enabled=screenid==math.floor(gn(31)) reverse=gb(4) -- enabled=gb(3) if not enabled then return end gpsx=gn(1) gpsy=gn(2) compass=gn(3) hdg=(compass*-360)%360 waypointx=gn(4) waypointy=gn(5) bearing=gn(6)
sn(3,compass) zoomm=gn(32) sn(32,zoomm) zoom=zoomm/1000 halfkm=zoomm/2 end
zoom=1 rowh=6 function onDraw()
-- debug -- screen.setColor(255,255,255) -- screen.drawText(0,0,string.format("%.0f",scr))
if not enabled then local label=reverse and "REV" or "DRILL" screen.setColor(0,255,0) screen.drawText(0,0,label) return end w=screen.getWidth() h=screen.getHeight() cx=w/2 cy=h/2
screen.setColor(0,0,0) screen.drawClear()
screen.drawMap(gpsx,gpsy,zoom)
-- Draw self blip in center of map screen.setColor(0,255,0) local t=-compass*math.pi*2 screen.drawLine(cx,cy,cx+math.sin(t)*5, cy-math.cos(t)*5)
screen.setColor(255,0,0) screen.drawCircleF(cx,cy,1)
-- Draw waypoint blip screen.setColor(0,0,255)
local dx=waypointx-gpsx local dy=gpsy-waypointy
-- screen.drawCircleF(cx + dx * w / zoomm, cy + dy * h/zoomm, 2) wx,wy=map.mapToScreen(gpsx,gpsy,zoom,w,h,waypointx,waypointy) screen.drawCircleF(wx,wy,2)
screen.setColor(0,0,255) local range=math.sqrt(dx^2+dy^2) local rangefmt
if range>1000 then rangefmt="%3.1fkm" range=range/1000 else rangefmt="%4.0fm" end
local txt=string.format("BRNG: %3.0f\nDIST: " .. rangefmt .. "\n%.0fkm",bearing,range,zoom) screen.drawText(0,0,txt) txt=string.format("%.0f, %.0f",gpsx,gpsy) screen.drawTextBox(0,h-rowh,w,h,txt) end
